### Requirements ###

bash, gawk, fetchmail

### Installing ###

1. Make sure that fetchmail is configured (POP3, no keep, etc).
2. Create configuration file $HOME/.mash.conf
   in which must be defined the following variables:
	TASKS_DIR           - location where the fetched tasks will be placed
	COMPLETED_TASKS_DIR - location where the completed tasks will be placed
	ABORTED_TASKS_DIR   - location where the aborted tasks will be placed
3. Add ./mash to crontab

